title: The Cottager to Her Infant
creator: William Wordsworth
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 13 recordings of The Cottager to Her Infant, by William Wordsworth. This was the Weekly Poetry project for January 2nd, 2011. Wordsworth was a defining member of the English Romantic Movement. Like other Romantics, Wordsworth’s personality and poetry were deeply influenced by his love of nature, especially by the sights and scenes of the Lake Country, in which he spent most of his mature life. A profoundly earnest and sincere thinker, he displayed a high seriousness tempered with tenderness and a love of simplicity. (summary from Bartleby.com) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, and for further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. Download M4B (7MB)
